# REFACTOR TASK: Add User-Configurable Grid Layout System to DeckForge

## CONCEPT
Instead of Claude deciding where components go on the slide, the USER picks a layout template from a visual menu. Each template defines the grid slots. Claude then fills those slots with the right content based on the prompt.

The flow becomes:
1. User types their prompt
2. User picks a layout (or gets a smart default)
3. Claude sees the layout + prompt, generates content FOR EACH SLOT
4. Composition engine places components in the grid
5. Render to .pptx

Implement Option C — smart default with override. Claude suggests a default layout based on the prompt. User can click "Change Layout" and pick a different one. Content reflows into the new layout.

